.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-patch-validate 1  "rom-weaver-patch-validate "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-patch\-validate \- Validate one or more ROM patch files against an input without writing output
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver patch validate\fR <\fB\-\-input\fR> [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-select\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-rom\-filter\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-filter\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-extract\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR] <\fB\-\-patch\fR> [\fB\-\-checksum\-cache\fR] [\fB\-\-validate\-with\-checksum\fR] [\fB\-\-validate\-with\-size\fR] [\fB\-\-validate\-with\-min\-size\fR] [\fB\-\-strip\-header\fR] [\fB\-\-n64\-byte\-order\fR] [\fB\-\-ignore\-checksum\-validation\fR] [\fB\-\-independent\fR] [\fB\-\-plan\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-basis\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-input\-check\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-output\-check\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Validate one or more ROM patch files against an input without writing output.
.PP
Validation performs the same patch\-format checksum checks as patch apply when the handler supports them, including VCDIFF/xdelta target\-window checksums. It also accepts optional input checksum and size values for source preflight.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-input\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
ROM or container input against which patches are validated
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-select\fR \fI<SELECT>\fR
Container payload selection pattern(s) used while auto\-extracting patch validate input and patch files
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-rom\-filter\fR
Keep ROM\-like payload candidates while resolving the patch validation input archive
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-filter\fR
Keep patch\-like payload candidates while resolving patch archives
.TP
\fB\-\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs (also enabled by ROM_WEAVER_LOG or RUST_LOG)
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-extract\fR
Disable container auto\-extract and validate the raw input and patch bytes directly
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR
Disable default ignore filtering during patch validate container payload resolution
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\fR \fI<PATCHES>\fR
Patch file(s) to validate in order; repeat \-\-patch for each step
.TP
\fB\-\-checksum\-cache\fR \fI<ALGO=HEX>\fR
Provide trusted effective patch input checksum values for validation without recomputing; repeat for multiple algorithms (for example: \-\-checksum\-cache crc32=1234abcd)
.TP
\fB\-\-validate\-with\-checksum\fR \fI<ALGO=HEX>\fR
Validate effective patch input checksum before patch preflight; repeat for multiple algorithms (for example: \-\-validate\-with\-checksum crc32=1234abcd)
.TP
\fB\-\-validate\-with\-size\fR \fI<BYTES>\fR
Validate exact effective patch input size before patch preflight
.TP
\fB\-\-validate\-with\-min\-size\fR \fI<BYTES>\fR
Validate minimum effective patch input size before patch preflight
.TP
\fB\-\-strip\-header\fR
Remove a detected ROM header before patch validation (A78/LNX/NES/FDS/SMC signatures; SNES/PCE copier\-size rules)
.TP
\fB\-\-n64\-byte\-order\fR \fI<N64_BYTE_ORDER>\fR
N64 byte order before patch validation: auto (default; match the patch source CRC32), keep, big\-endian, little\-endian, or byte\-swapped
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
keep
.IP \(bu 2
big\-endian
.IP \(bu 2
little\-endian
.IP \(bu 2
byte\-swapped
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-ignore\-checksum\-validation\fR
Skip patch\-provided checksum validation during patch validation and permit recoverable patch\-format validation issues
.TP
\fB\-\-independent\fR
Validate each \-\-patch independently against the original input (no sequential chaining); report a per\-patch verdict and never abort the batch on a single failing patch
.TP
\fB\-\-plan\fR
Resolve every patch\*(Aqs input basis and chain order statically and report a typed verification plan; runs preflight only for patches that consume the original input
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-basis\fR \fI<PATCH_BASIS>\fR
What the preceding \-\-patch\*(Aqs input checks were authored against: auto (infer from checksums), base (the original ROM), or previous (the prior patch\*(Aqs output); binds to the most recent \-\-patch
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
base
.IP \(bu 2
previous
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-input\-check\fR \fI<ALGO=HEX>\fR
Declared input checks for the preceding \-\-patch (comma\-separable ALGO=HEX tokens; empty skips); binds to the most recent \-\-patch
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-output\-check\fR \fI<ALGO=HEX>\fR
Declared output checks for the preceding \-\-patch (comma\-separable ALGO=HEX tokens; empty skips); binds to the most recent \-\-patch
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<auto|N>\fR [default: auto]
Thread budget: auto or a positive integer
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
